{"body": "To be fair, I can see the 'needs of the many vs needs of the few' argument (where 'the many' is defined as those who want the default stack, and 'the few' is defined as those who want to customize things).\r\n\r\nI can understand the desire not to add noise to the application `Gemfile`s of 'the many' (ie., the desire not to devolve the dependencies from `rails.gemspec` into generated `Gemfile`s). However, I don't see how that would be a 'flimsy' approach. Explicit, yes. Noisy, perhaps. I just don't see what's 'flimsy' about it.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1451231", "created_at": "2011-06-27T23:28:44Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1855#issuecomment-1451231", "updated_at": "2011-06-27T23:28:44Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1855, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/emmanuel", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/83611ed7f7ed587603fbdffc691ea989?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F82674fc29bc0d9895cee346548c2cb5c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/received_events", "gravatar_id": "83611ed7f7ed587603fbdffc691ea989", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "emmanuel", "type": "User", "id": 7657, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/emmanuel/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52384d2bbd3543c1510114a2"}, "id": 1451231, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1855"}
